HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 294
BY REPRESENTATIVE ORGERON
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Recognizes June 2, 2026, as National Mississippi River
Day
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To recognize June 2, 2026, as National Mississippi River Day, urging all people to celebrate,
3 protect, and restore the Mississippi River and its watershed by participating in
4 events, signing up as One Mississippi "River Citizens", and taking action to
5 safeguard this invaluable resource for generations to come.
6 WHEREAS, the Mississippi River is one of our nation's most iconic and vital
7 waterways, spanning approximately two thousand three hundred fifty miles from Minnesota
8 to Louisiana and uniting ten mainstem states and thirty-two tributary states in its watershed;
9 and
10 WHEREAS, the Mississippi River has been deeply woven into the lives of
11 indigenous peoples for thousands of years, sustaining communities through nourishment,
12 travel, and trade while also holding profound cultural, spiritual, and ancestral significance;
13 and
14 WHEREAS, the Mississippi River serves as a critical source of drinking water for
15 over twenty million Americans, a vital habitat for diverse fish and wildlife, and a powerful
16 economic engine supporting commerce, agriculture, tourism, and recreation; and
17 WHEREAS, the river supplies the heart of a migratory flyway for sixty percent of
18 North America's bird species, provides habitat for at least two hundred sixty fish species, and
19 sustains numerous amphibians, reptiles, and mammals, making it one of the world's most
20 important ecological corridors; and
21 WHEREAS, the health of the Mississippi River is under threat from pollution, habitat
22 loss, climate change, and other environmental stressors, which impact the communities,
23 economies, and ecosystems that depend on it; and
