1 WHEREAS, protecting and restoring the Mississippi River requires collaboration
2 across states, agencies, organizations, individuals, and communities to implement
3 sustainable and regenerative conservation practices, to restore wetlands and floodplains, and
4 to reduce agricultural and urban runoff to improve water quality; and
5 WHEREAS, the Mississippi River connects millions of people, reflecting our shared
6 history, culture, and responsibility to ensure its vitality for future generations; and
7 WHEREAS, One Mississippi is a national outreach and advocacy organization
8 dedicated to protecting, restoring, and strengthening the Mississippi River by connecting a
9 growing community of over twenty thousand "River Citizens" to take action on issues
10 regarding the river's water quality, wildlife, and surrounding communities; and
11 WHEREAS, One Mississippi and its network of seventy-eight organizations and
12 "River Citizens" are inviting the public to take action, whether through conservation efforts,
13 advocacy, or simply enjoying the river and building community; and
14 WHEREAS, One Mississippi's upcoming River Days of Action event, which will be
15 held June 1st through 15th, provides a perfect opportunity for people across the region to
16 come together to restore, celebrate, and advocate for a healthier river.
17 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
18 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby recognize June 2, 2026, as National Mississippi River
19 Day, urging all people to celebrate, protect, and restore the Mississippi River and its
20 watershed by participating in events, signing up as One Mississippi "River Citizens", and
21 taking action to safeguard this invaluable resource for generations to come.
